<h3>
    What is ESA (Eve Swagger Auth)?
</h3>
<p>
    ESA is a SaaS (software as a service) application for Eve online. ESA is designed to make the managing of in game groups easy for both the individual member and the leader of the groups.
    Upon registration users will be able to create their own subdomain within the ESA site, this will then allow users to configure the site the way they want it.
</p>
<h3>What are the Features of ESA?</h3>
<p>
    Upon launch ESA will focus on the configuration of Discord servers based on in game relationships but based on demand and requests I am hoping to expand this to lots of different features including the management of alt accounts and one 
    day an online fitting tool. For a full list of planned features please visit the sites <a href="https://trello.com/b/mJ44Tdy0/eve-swagger-auth" target="_blank">Trello page</a>.
</p>

<h3>What sort of configuration can I do?</h3>
<p>The relationships that will be configurable on launch will be:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Static Groups - assign permissions to static entities such as characters/corporations/alliances and factions</li>
    <li>Standings - standings from one entity to another, most useful for your own groups standings but in theory could be setup to let all of Joe Bloggs blues into a given channel.</li>
    <li>In Game Roles/Titles - based on the roles given to a character in game</li>
    
</ul>
<p>Relationships that need some work, like all the good ones:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Fleet - this one is my favourite, allow people to say I am going to be a fleet commander link the fleet in the third party tool and you can automatically give permissions to channels and move the characters into fleet.</li>
    <li>War Based - this one is on the back burner because it didn't seem that useful but still interesting. Assign based on if they are a war ally or if they are at war with you. As I said not the most useful.</li>
    <li>Ship class ownership - so many people have a capital channel and a super capital channel, make this easy by allowing access based on the ships that the member owns. Currently supercaps and capitals implemented but no reason that 
    it couldn't be expanded to other class types</li>
</ul>


