<h3>Where is my data stored?</h3>
<p>
    ESA uses several MS SQL databases we have one static data database that is restored from the static data dump, one tenant data database that holds information about each tenant, basically just their name and some other info about what links 
    to third parties they have setup. For individual tenants we create the same database schema for each that contains a the configuration and any SSO keys as well as any data that is pulled from the API. To speed up load times any public data is 
    stored in the public version of the tenant database. This means that only one person has to wait around for the public data to be pulled the first time then everyone gets to use the cache after that. If you want me to provide a backup of your 
    database just ask I will also delete it upon request however I will need in game confirmation from the person who created the group. Eventually this will be an automated process.
</p>

